subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is currently known from southern Cuanza-Sul, central Huambo and northern Benguela Provinces, Angola (Fig. 
1
). It appears to have a relatively large, but patchy, distribution on the Angolan highlands and may extend its range into neighbouring provinces. Although sometimes locally common, it appears to be absent from vast areas in-between, where the species would be expected to occur. Populations in isolated granite outcrops may be threatened by removal of rock flakes for construction of homes and other buildings.
